            "type": "text",
            "text": "Introduction"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Qwen3 TTS VoiceDesign API provides a robust solution for generating natural-sounding speech from text, leveraging a 1.7B parameter model optimized for 12Hz audio output. This guide offers practical, technical insights for experienced API teams looking to integrate and scale this API in production environments."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Overview of Qwen3 TTS VoiceDesign API Capabilities"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Qwen3 TTS VoiceDesign API is built on the Qwen3_TTS_12Hz_1_7B_VoiceDesign model, designed for high-fidelity voice synthesis with customizable voice profiles. Key features include support for multiple languages, adjustable speech parameters, and low-latency responses suitable for real-time applications. The API exposes RESTful endpoints that accept text input and return audio data in formats like WAV or MP3, making it compatible with standard web and mobile infrastructures."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Quick Start Guide for Qwen3 TTS VoiceDesign API Integration"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "To begin using the Qwen3 TTS VoiceDesign API, first obtain an API key from the provider's dashboard. Authentication is handled via HTTP headers; include your key in the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Authorization",
            "code": true
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " field as "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Bearer <your-api-key>",
            "code": true
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". A basic API call involves sending a POST request to the synthesis endpoint with a JSON payload containing the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "text",
            "code": true
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " field. For example:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "code_block",
        "lang": "bash",
        "value": "curl -X POST https://api.example.com/v1/tts \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_KEY\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"text\": \"Hello, world!\", \"voice_id\": \"default\"}'",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "code_line",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "curl -X POST https://api.example.com/v1/tts \\"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "code_line",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "  -H \"Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_KEY\" \\"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "code_line",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "code_line",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "  -d '{\"text\": \"Hello, world!\", \"voice_id\": \"default\"}'"
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "This returns an audio stream that can be saved or played directly. Ensure error handling for HTTP status codes like 429 (rate limits) or 500 (server errors) to maintain reliability."
          }
        ]
      },
