            "type": "text",
            "text": "Optimizing Performance and Handling Errors in Production"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For production use, implement caching for frequently requested text-to-speech conversions to reduce latency and API costs. Use asynchronous processing for batch requests to avoid blocking operations. Monitor API usage with metrics like response time and error rates, and set up alerts for anomalies. Handle common errors such as invalid input by validating text length and encoding before sending requests. Additionally, consider implementing retry logic with exponential backoff for transient failures to ensure robust integration."
